node.text: Your sensual power is within you *now*, no exceptions. Not only does sexual vitality bring more joy and pleasure to life, but it can help to balance hormones, reduce cortisol levels, and revitalize every system from the skin to your metabolism. At the link in bio, discover how to tap into this creative, potent source—no matter life's roadblocks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sakara Life on August 08, 2021. May be an image of fig.

node.text:
"Figs" by D.H. Lawrence, 1923

The proper way to eat a fig, in society,
Is to split it in four, holding it by the stump,
And open it, so that it is a glittering, rosy, moist, honied, heavy-petalled four-petalled flower.

Then you throw away the skin
Which is just like a four-sepalled calyx,
After you have taken off the blossom with your lips.

But the vulgar way
Is just to put your mouth to the crack, and take out the flesh in one bite.

Every fruit has its secret.

node.text:
Match the vibrance of a summer night with a glass of chilled, gluggable natural red wine—punched up with antioxidant-rich extras. Our Sparkling Stone Fruit Sangria alchemizes two wines; adds a squeeze of lemon; muddles a mix of grapefruit, plum, and apple; and a sprig of rosemary for nostalgia. This drink is designed to activate your pleasure centers. 

Take in the intoxicating fragrances and relish in a refreshing PM ritual—the full recipe is waiting for you at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sakara Life on August 05, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Whip up this smoothie, featuring our Organic Protein + Greens Super Powder, to flush toxins, nourish the gut microbiome, and naturally elevate energy levels. It's simple yet highly effective—we like to think of it as the last smoothie recipe you'll ever need.

½ banana, frozen
1 large handful spinach
1 cup unsweetened plant milk
1 tablespoon nut/seed butter
1 serving of Sakara Organic Protein + Greens Super Powder

Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth and creamy. Optional: sweeten to taste with a bit of maple syrup or raw honey. Enjoy mindfully and with gratitude ✨

node.text:
Summer is about releasing inhibitions...a season where self-criticism or comparison only slows down your lifelong pursuit of seeking more of what lights YOU up. Your beauty is defined by you, and only you. 

This notion reminded us of the poignant (and viral) piece on #SLifeMag, in which @hi_soy_gabby explored the freedom in her “extra” 5-10 pounds. It’s vulnerable, relatable, and might even kickstart your own inside-out beauty revolution. Recommended reading for all, at the link in bio.

node.text:
Tonight marks the first sunset of August.

Use three minutes to take some slow belly breaths and feel into your physical body. Exhale deeply. In this moment of stillness, jot down one intention you have for the fiery month ahead. What do you wish to call in? Whether it's personal, professional, health-related, about love or self-discovery... we want to know, Sakaralites.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sakara Life on August 01, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: We've got a crush on this breakfast. It's undeniably pretty, tastes fruit-forward, juicy, and has notes of strawberry-vanilla...but the health benefits are what really have us falling in love. At the link in bio, find the recipe for the Endless Summer Rose Chia Parfait.
